The paper focuses on the development of a system for exploring and analyzing text-based social media data, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of domain models and extractors, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of REST-based service APIs, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the architecture and underlying analytics of the system, which could potentially fall under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL).
